instruction:
Write a function `mainTasks` that takes three parameters:
* `tasks` - a list of strings with the names of all tasks, an array;
* `toDoFirst` - a string with the name of the first task of interest;
* `toDoLast` - string with the name of the last task of interest.

The function must return an object with the properties `toDoFirst` and `toDoLast`, where:
* the `toDoFirst` value is the `Before task_before` string, where `task_before` is the name of the task following `toDoFirst` in the `tasks` array;
* The value of `toDoLast` is the string `After task_after`, where `task_after` is the name of the task that precedes `toDoLast` in the `tasks` array.

Conditions:
* `toDoLast` always follows `toDoFirst` in the `tasks` array;
* Only unique values can be in the `tasks` array;
* There are always at least two elements in the `tasks` array;
* strings can include spaces.

Examples of running a function:
```javascript
mainTasks(["Getting up", "Working", "Eating", "Reading", "Sleeping"], "Getting up", "Reading"); // { "Getting up": "Before Working", "Reading": "After Eating" }
mainTasks(["Fist", "Second", "Third", "Fourth", "Fifth", "Sixth"], "Third", "Fourth"); // { "Third": "Before Fourth", "Fourth": "After Third" }
```
